The paper deals with the analysis of satellite images using deep learning techniques, specifically Convolutional and Recurrent Neural Networks. This falls under the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a new architecture for time series classification, which involves the use of neural networks, which could also be classified under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning approaches in remote sensing, which could fall under Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of large amounts of data, which could also be classified under Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
